# functionTeamPresenceChangeWebhook
**Description**
This project seeks to bring your Teams Presence status into Hubitat Elevation Smart home hub and WebCore, a free and open-source solution for home automation, for simplified control of a Busy Light or enable much more elaborate automations using any of the thousands of supported devices.

**Problem or Opportunity**
Working from Home (WfH) means sharing space at your home with both your co-workers and your family. Teams Presence status tells our co-workers about our availability, but our families are often left to wonder. Having Teams Presence in your Smart Home environment will empower you to show your Presence Status using any method that suits you.

Teams "Busy Lights" are a popular way to signal our status to those physically around us, but they often have several problems, including:

1. Most are difficult and complex to set up
2. Supported hardware is either limited or proprietary
3. Often rely on polling to get status which is slow and taxing on the service
4. Can require running an app/service the computer where Teams is running
5. This solution would integrate with any device in an instance of Home Assistant and will receive notifications of changes as they happen to eliminate the need for polling.

**Solution**
1. Made a python script for Authenticating with MS Tenant and Subscribing to MS Graph /presence Subscription (teamspresencechange.py )
2. Azure Function function that acts like a middle layer between  **MS Graph Sub** and my **WebCore instance** (Rule Machine for my Hubitat home environment)
   Basically, this function is
    a) Sending a status code 202 back to MS Graph sub
    b) Parsing the JSON sub response and extracting the values for "availability" and "activity"
    c) sending these two variables to the webcore webhook as json content

  https://github.com/vsterian/functionTeamPresenceChangeWebhook/tree/master/**webhookMSteamsPresenceChange**

3. Webcore piston, which based on the "availability" and "activity" is able to perform customizable actions. For now, just changing a bulb color based on the MS Teams availability
